sentences.english: The biggest oceangoing ships on the North Atlantic arrived and departed.
sentences.chinese: 那些北大西洋上最大的远洋船到达了，离开了。

sentences.english: It was the geological chaos that created the North Atlantic Ocean.
sentences.chinese: 彼时发生了一场形成今日北大西洋的地质混乱。

sentences.english: A significant secular increase has occurred in particulate pollution over the North Atlantic.
sentences.chinese: 在北大西洋上粒子的污染明显地逐年增加。

sentences.english: Two-thirds of North Atlantic cod catches are believed to go unreported.
sentences.chinese: 有三分之二的北大西洋鳕鱼捕获量被认为是没有报告。

sentences.english: The rugged weather of the North Atlantic frightens me.
sentences.chinese: 北大西洋狂暴的天气使我害怕。

sentences.english: This image shows a manifestation of the North Atlantic bloom west of Iceland.
sentences.chinese: 这张图像显示了冰岛西面的北大西洋爆发的表现。

sentences.english: The "Queen Elizabeth" and the "France" are on the North Atlantic run.
sentences.chinese: “伊丽莎白女王号”和“法国号”正在北大西洋航行。

sentences.english: NATO (1-7) in the United States under the North Atlantic Treaty of foreigners and their relevant staff.
sentences.chinese: 根据北大西洋公约驻美的外国人及其有关人员。

sentences.english: Vanguard Class submarines routinely spend weeks at a time underwater on patrol in the North Atlantic.
sentences.chinese: 先锋号在北大西洋上执行为期数周的水下例行巡逻。

sentences.english: Thy cables breathe the North Atlantic still.
sentences.chinese: 您的巨缆依然吞吐着北大西洋。

definition: Aleutian Islands (trailing 2250 km southwest of Alaska almost down to Kamtchatka)
